The paper deals with a source coding problem for a multidimensional Gauss-Markov process, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The use of mean squared-error (MSE) distortion as a performance criterion suggests that the paper may also fall under the sub-category of signal processing (cs.SP). The paper also mentions the use of a closed form expression for stationary scalar-valued Gaussian processes, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper deals with a remote source coding problem, which may fall under the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI) as it involves communication between different nodes.
